{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782958624,"nonce":"13JaUxJfJRwHuQySYoDcRgYCVgY=","kind":"spec","title":"Archive lifecycle — design","content_type":"text/markdown"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782958624,"nonce":"PKgd8G2vz5Iw7g2Xa3Q14TUQ+E0=","body":"# Archive lifecycle — design\n\n- **Date:** 2026-06-27\n- **Status:** Approved (pending implementation)\n- **Scope:** a new hidden lifecycle state for entries, distinct from tombstone.\n\n## Decisions\n\n- **D1 — separate boolean axis.** Add `Snapshot.Archived bool`, independent of\n  `Status`. Archiving an `obsolete` entry keeps it `obsolete` *and* hides it.\n- **D2 — ops.** New append-only `Archive` (Archived=true) and `Unarchive`\n  (Archived=false) ops, mirroring `Tombstone`/`Restore` but **not** touching\n  `Status`. Registered in `operationUnmarshaler` and `Entry.Log()`\n  (`archive`/`unarchive`).\n- **D3 — store.** `Store.Archive(id)` / `Store.Unarchive(id)` (tier search +\n  append + commit, `SetKind` shape). `ListFilter` gains `IncludeArchived` and\n  `ArchivedOnly`. Filter in `List`:\n  ```\n  if f.ArchivedOnly \u0026\u0026 !snap.Archived { continue }\n  if snap.Archived \u0026\u0026 !f.ArchivedOnly \u0026\u0026 !f.IncludeArchived { continue }\n  ```\n- **D4 — commands (lifecycle group).**\n  - `kref archive \u003cid|path\u003e` — archive one entry.\n  - `kref archive --obsolete` — archive every non-archived `obsolete` entry,\n    after a confirmation. `\u003cid\u003e` xor `--obsolete`; one required.\n  - `kref unarchive \u003cid|path\u003e` — clear the flag.\n  - `kref list --archived` — show only archived (→ `ArchivedOnly`). `--all`\n    keeps showing everything (→ `IncludeArchived`, alongside the existing\n    include-deleted).\n- **D5 — confirmation.** The `--obsolete` bulk prompts on stderr\n  `Archive N obsolete entr(y/ies)? Type y to proceed: `; proceeds on\n  `y`/`yes`/`Yes` (case-insensitive `y` or `yes`), aborts otherwise. `-y/--yes`\n  skips the prompt. Reuses the `bufio.NewReader(cmd.InOrStdin())` pattern from\n  `reconcile`.\n- **D6 — render.** Archived entries (shown under `--archived`/`--all`) get an\n  `(archived)` title suffix, mirroring `(deleted)`.\n\n## Out of scope (YAGNI)\n\nNo `archived` column, no auto-archive policies, no change to `tidy`/`whatsnew`/\nsync. Archive is purely a visibility flag plus the two commands.\n\n## Testing (TDD)\n\n- entry: `Archive`/`Unarchive` Apply; unmarshal round-trip; Log mapping.\n- store: archived hidden by default; shown under `ArchivedOnly` and\n  `IncludeArchived`; `Unarchive` reverses; status preserved across archive.\n- cmd: single archive/unarchive; `--archived` view; `--obsolete` bulk with the\n  prompt and `-y`; `\u003cid\u003e` xor `--obsolete` errors; render `(archived)` suffix."}]}